    {
      "id": "DnEU",
      "code_hash": "3fd4540d234761b2c6e86dc853e2aa44",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"7-strategic-insights\">7 \u00b7 Strategic Insights</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><strong>Key takeaways from the sweeps above:</strong></span>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Dragon escort is high-value</strong> \u2014 6,000 pts (2\u00d73,000) from minute 12 onwards. Always contest if you have the numbers.</li>\n<li><strong>Strongholds dominate late-game</strong> \u2014 4\u00d7180 = 720 pts/min from minute 12. The first-capture bonus (4\u00d7600 = 2,400) is also the largest.</li>\n<li><strong>Outposts are early-game anchors</strong> \u2014 cheap to hold, steady 80 pts/min income from minute 0.</li>\n<li><strong>Armory + Hot Spring</strong> \u2014 moderate value (120 pts/min each) but also grant combat buffs (50% stats / 100% heal speed).</li>\n<li><strong>Player advantage compounds</strong> \u2014 even a small numbers advantage (e.g. 60v40) lets you contest more objectives simultaneously.</li>\n<li><strong>Against defensive opponents</strong> \u2014 push center and strongholds harder; they won't contest your outposts.</li>\n<li><strong>Against aggressive opponents</strong> \u2014 defend your outposts and let them overextend.</li>\n</ol></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    }
  ]
